'''Morgan Elliot Rogers''' (born 26 July 2002) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|AstonVil}} club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] and the [[England national football team|England national team]]. A versatile player across attacking positions, Rogers is known for his strength, attacking runs, ability to score from a distance and ball control.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":13" /><ref name=":0" /><ref name=":4" />

Born in [[Halesowen]] in the [[Dudley Metropolitan Borough]], Rogers is a product of the [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] academy. He signed for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in 2019, but did not make an appearance for the club, and after loan spells at [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]], [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] and [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]], he joined [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] in 2023. After half a season at the club, Rogers signed for Aston Villa for a reported fee of £8 million in 2024. Following a breakout season with Villa in which he was named their young player of the season, Rogers won the [[PFA Young Player of the Year]] award in 2025.

Rogers has represented England at international levels from under 15 to senior level, making his senior international debut in 2024.

== Early life ==
Born in [[Halesowen]], Rogers is the middle child in a family of three brothers born to Deborah and Howard Rogers.<ref name=":5">{{Cite news |last1=Tanswell |first1=Jacob |last2=Madeley |first2=Steve |date=2024-02-01 |title=Morgan Rogers' journey from West Brom wonderkid to Aston Villa – via Man City and Middlesbrough |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5234870/2024/02/01/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-transfer/ |access-date=2025-04-02 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=":11">{{Cite web |last=Jacob |first=Gary |date=29 December 2025 |title=Can Morgan Rogers complete perfect year with Aston Villa and England? |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-england-world-cup-sm596rgzz |access-date=7 January 2026 |website=www.thetimes.com |language=en}}</ref> He attended Colley Lane Primary and [[Sandwell Academy]],<ref name=":5" /> and was part of the Sandwell team that won the National Schools Cup in 2017, scoring and assisting in the final.<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |last=Dick |first=Brian |date=2019-03-21 |title=The rise and rise of Morgan Rogers – what you need to know |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/west-bromwich-youngster-morgan-rogers-15143289 |access-date=2025-04-02 |website=Birmingham Live |language=en}}</ref> Rogers was a childhood fan of [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tanswell |first=Jacob |date=2021-09-07 |title=My friend Morgan Rogers – from the playground to the Premier League |url=https://www.dorset.live/sport/football/football-news/friend-morgan-rogers-bournemouth-loanees-5881683 |access-date=2025-04-02 |website=Dorset Live |language=en}}</ref> and a childhood friend of fellow footballer [[Jude Bellingham]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jolly |first=Richard |date=19 March 2025 |title=The rise of Morgan Rogers: 'Unai Emery battered me over one little thing' |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/morgan-rogers-england-tuchel-emery-bellingham-henderson-b2717926.html |access-date=8 August 2025 |website=The Independent |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==

===West Bromwich Albion===

Rogers joined West Bromwich Albion at the age of seven, after being spotted by a club scout.<ref name=":6" /> He made his professional debut for West Brom on 6 February 2019, coming on as an 82nd-minute substitute for [[Wes Hoolahan]] against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in the [[FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47037236 |title=West Bromwich Albion 1–3 Brighton & Hove Albion |date=6 February 2019 |accessdate=6 February 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
Rogers signed for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on 1 August 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Manchester City sign England youth international Morgan Rogers from West Brom |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11775285/manchester-city-sign-england-youth-international-morgan-rogers-from-west-brom |website=skysports.com |accessdate=30 October 2019 |date=1 August 2019}}</ref>

====Lincoln City (loan)====
On 4 January 2021, Rogers signed for [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |title= Imps sign highly rated Manchester City forward on loan |url= https://www.weareimps.com/news/2021/january/210104-morgan-rogers/ |publisher=[[Lincoln City F.C.]] |accessdate=4 January 2021}}</ref> He made his debut for the club against [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]] a few days later, coming off the bench.<ref>{{cite web |title=Match Report – Peterborough (H)|url=https://www.weareimps.com/news/2021/january/210109-peterborough-match-report/|publisher=[[Lincoln City F.C.]] |accessdate=9 January 2021}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal against [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] in a 1–0 win on 26 January.<ref>{{cite web |title=Match Report – Portsmouth (A)|url=https://www.weareimps.com/news/2021/january/210126-portsmouth/|publisher=[[Lincoln City F.C.]] |accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref> Three goals in seven games during the month of March contributed to his winning the [[EFL Young Player of the Month]] award during his loan spell.<ref name="Morgan Rogers picks up EFL Young Player of the Month award for March">{{cite web |title=Morgan Rogers picks up EFL Young Player of the Month award for March|url=https://www.weareimps.com/news/2021/april/210412-morgan-rogers/|publisher=[[Lincoln City F.C.]] |accessdate=12 April 2021}}</ref>

====Bournemouth (loan)====
On 23 August 2021, Rogers signed for [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afcb.co.uk/news/first-team/rogers-joins-the-cherries-on-loan/|title = Rogers joins the Cherries on loan}}</ref> Rogers found his first-team opportunities at Bournemouth limited, and was confined to mostly substitute appearances during the season.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-11-17 |title=Rogers has 'a big quality' in waiting |url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/daily-echo-rogers-has-a-big-quality-in/178442338/ |access-date=2025-08-08 |work=Daily Echo |pages=M45}}</ref> He scored his only goal for the club on 15 January 2022, in a 3–2 [[EFL Championship|Championship]] defeat against [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Bournemouth beaten by late Luton goal |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59918635 |access-date=15 January 2022}}</ref>

====Blackpool (loan)====
On 4 January 2023, Rogers joined [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=FC |first=Blackpool |title=Blackpool Confirm Loan Signing of Morgan Rogers From Manchester City |url=https://blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/2023/january/04/blackpool-confirm-loan-signing-of-morgan-rogers-from-manchester-city/ |access-date=4 January 2023 |website=Blackpool FC |language=en}}</ref> He scored his only goal for the club in a 1–0 win against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on 8 May 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 May 2023 |title=Norwich City 0–1 Blackpool: Morgan Rogers seals win for relegated Tangerines |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12873866/norwich-city-0-1-blackpool-morgan-rogers-seals-win-for-relegated-tangerines |access-date=15 November 2024 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref>

=== Middlesbrough ===
On 7 July 2023, Rogers signed for Championship club [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite news |date=7 July 2023 |title=Boro sign Glover, Rogers and Silvera |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66126902 |access-date=7 July 2023}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 29 July, a late equaliser to make it 2–2 in a [[Exhibition game|pre-season friendly]] against [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.mfc.co.uk/news/2023/july/29/Match-Report-Boro-2-AJ-Auxerre-2/ | title=Match Report Boro 2 AJ Auxerre 2 | date=29 July 2023 }}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the club on 29 August in a 3–1 [[EFL Cup]] win against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.mfc.co.uk/news/2023/august/29/Match-Review--Bolton-1-Boro-3/ | title=Match Review: Bolton 1 Boro 3 | date=29 August 2023 }}</ref>

Rogers scored five times during Middlesbrough's run to the [[2023–24 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] semi-finals, making him the competition's top goalscorer for the season.<ref name="eflc">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/league-cup/top-scorers|title=EFL Cup Top Scorers|access-date=8 April 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

=== Aston Villa ===
[[File:St. Louis City vs Aston Villa (Jul 2025) 15.jpg|thumb|Rogers playing for Aston Villa in 2025]]
On 1 February 2024, 21-year-old Rogers signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] for an undisclosed fee,<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=1 February 2024 |title=Aston Villa announce Morgan Rogers signing |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2024/february/01/villa-announce-rogers-signing/ |access-date=1 February 2024 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref> reported to be £8m, potentially rising to £15m with performance-related add-ons.<ref>{{Cite news |date=1 February 2024 |title=Villa sign forward Rogers from Middlesbrough |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68154784 |access-date=1 February 2024 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Manchester City were entitled to 25% of the fee, due to a sell-on clause in the original transfer to Middlesbrough.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Ben |date=30 January 2024 |title=Aston Villa agree £15m deal to sign Morgan Rogers from Middlesbrough |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/jan/30/aston-villa-agree-15m-deal-to-sign-morgan-rogers-from-middlesbrough |access-date=1 February 2024 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 3 February, Rogers made his Premier League debut as a late substitute in a 5–0 victory away at [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sheffield United 0–5 Aston Villa: Unai Emery's side run riot at Bramall Lane to move back into top four |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13060822/sheffield-united-0-5-aston-villa-unai-emerys-side-run-riot-at-bramall-lane-to-move-back-into-top-four |access-date=5 February 2024 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

On 6 April 2024, Rogers scored his first goal for Aston Villa in a 3–3 draw against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].<ref>{{cite news |date=6 April 2024 |first=Joe |last=Rindl |title=Aston Villa 3–3 Brentford: Late Watkins goal earns point for Villa |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68697128 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=6 April 2024 |language=en}}</ref> On 29 January 2025, he netted his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goals by scoring a [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]], including two in the first five minutes, in a 4–2 victory over [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in which he was named player of the match.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tanswell |first1=Jacob |last2=Carey |first2=Mark |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6097221/2025/01/29/aston-villa-celtic-duran-watkins-rogers/ |title=Aston Villa 4 Celtic 2 – Mission accomplished, Rogers' first hat-trick but farewell Duran? |work=The New York Times |date=29 January 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/rogers-lauds-champions-league-hat-225100820.html |title=Rogers lauds Champions League hat-trick as career high |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=29 January 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Tanswell |first=Jacob |title=Uncertainty gripped the futures of Duran and Watkins at Aston Villa – Rogers stepped forward |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6096742/2025/01/30/duran-watkins-transfers-rogers-aston-villa/ |access-date=2025-01-30 |work=The New York Times |date=30 January 2025 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In doing so, he became the second youngest English player to score a hat-trick in the competition.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Brewin |first=John |date=2025-01-30 |title=Champions League review: smaller teams struggle but new stars rise |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jan/30/champions-league-review-smaller-teams-struggle-as-new-stars-rise |access-date=2025-01-30 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On April 10, 2025, Aston Villa lost 3–1 to [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Quarter-finals|Champions League quarterfinal]] first leg; Rogers scored Aston Villa's only goal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-09 |title=Morgan Rogers insists Aston Villa 'not done yet' despite defeat to 'deadly' PSG |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-psg-champions-league-b2730565.html |access-date=2025-04-10 |website=The Independent |language=en}}</ref>

After a breakout [[2024–25 Aston Villa F.C. season|2024–25 season]] in which he scored 14 goals and provided 15 assists across all competitions,<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 August 2025 |title=Three elite clubs pushing to sign Aston Villa star in major move |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/three-elite-clubs-pushing-sign-135000406.html |access-date=29 August 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> Rogers was named Aston Villa's Young Player of the Season at the club's end of season awards.<ref name=":7">{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2025-05-21 |title=Tielemans scoops End of Season Awards double |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2025/may/21/2025-player-awards-winners-men/ |access-date=2025-05-22 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref> On 19 June 2025, it was announced that Rogers was one of six nominees for the [[PFA Young Player of the Year]] award,<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 June 2025 |title=PFA Young Player of the Year nominees announced |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cj4edzw9qxeo |access-date=19 June 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> which he then went on to win – becoming the fifth Aston Villa player to win the award since its inception.<ref name=":9">{{Cite web |last=Club |first=Aston Villa Football |date=2025-08-19 |title=Morgan Rogers crowned PFA Young Player of the Year |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2025/august/19/rogers-crowned-pfa-young-player-of-the-year/ |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref>

On 10 November 2025, Rogers signed a contract extension with Aston Villa until 2031.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-10 |title=Morgan Rogers pens new deal |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2025/november/10/contract-rogers-pens-new-deal/ |access-date=2025-11-10 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref> On 20 May 2026, he scored in a 3–0 win over [[SC Freiburg]] in the [[2026 UEFA Europa League final|Europa League final]] as his club won the competition for the first time in their history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/02a5-20ac3759bba4-7f91e47690b9-1000--freiburg-0-3-aston-villa-rampant-villans-win-europa-leagu/ |title=Freiburg 0-3 Aston Villa: Brilliant Villans win Europa League for the first time |publisher=UEFA |date=20 May 2026 }}</ref> [[UEFA]] subsequently named Rogers the [[UEFA Europa League#Awards|Europa League Player of the Season]].<ref name=":15">{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |date=2026-05-21 |title=Morgan Rogers named 2025/26 UEFA Europa League Player of the Season {{!}} UEFA Europa League |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/02a5-20ada4582a19-a671041d6e0e-1000--morgan-rogers-named-2025-26-uefa-europa-league-player-of-/ |access-date=2026-05-21 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref>

==International career ==
Rogers has represented England at all international levels from under-15 to senior.<ref name="Youth">{{cite web|title=The rise and rise of West Brom's Morgan Rogers – what you need to know|url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/west-bromwich-youngster-morgan-rogers-15143289|publisher=Birmingham Mail|date=12 September 2018|accessdate=6 February 2019}}</ref>

He represented the [[England national under-16 football team|England under-16 team]] at the [[Montaigu Tournament|2018 Montaigu Tournament]].<ref name="Youth"/> In September 2018, Rogers scored a [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] for the [[England national under-17 football team|England under-17 team]] in a game against [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium]].<ref name="Youth"/> The following month saw him score against the [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|United States]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2018/oct/12/england-u17s-usa-report-121018|title=Young Lions stage second-half comeback in Chester to beat USA in tournament opener|date=12 October 2018|accessdate=20 April 2019|publisher=The Football Association}}</ref> as well as scoring the final goal in a 3–1 victory against [[Brazil national under-17 football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2018/oct/16/england-u17s-brazil-report-161018|title=A memorable night in Telford for the Young Lions as they see off the South Americans|date=16 October 2018|accessdate=20 April 2019|publisher=The Football Association}}</ref> In March 2019, Rogers scored twice in an elite qualifier against [[Switzerland national under-17 football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2019/mar/21/england-u17s-switzerland-report-210319|title=Young Lions make five-star start to their Euro elite qualifying round with Swiss win|date=21 March 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019|publisher=The Football Association}}</ref> In April 2019, Rogers was included in the England squad for the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2019/may/02/england-u17s-squad-named-for-euro-finals-020519|title=Young Lions squad head for UEFA U17 EURO Finals in the Republic of Ireland this month|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=2 April 2019|publisher=The Football Association.}}</ref>

Rogers made his [[England national under-18 football team|England under-18]] debut as a 64th minute substitute during a 3–2 win over [[Australia national under-18 soccer team|Australia]] on 6 September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2019/sep/06/england-u18s-3-2-australia-060919|title=ALEX MIGHTEN BLASTS HAT-TRICK TO FIRE ENGLAND U18S TO VICTORY OVER AUSTRALIA|date=6 September 2019|accessdate=7 September 2019|publisher=The Football Association.}}</ref>

On 6 September 2021, Rogers made his debut for the [[England national under-20 football team|England U20s]] during a 6–1 victory over [[Romania national under-20 football team|Romania U20s]] at [[St George's Park National Football Centre|St. George's Park]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Six at SGP for MU20s|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2021/Sep/06/20210609-england-mu20s-romania-match-report|access-date=6 September 2021|website=EnglandFootball.com}}</ref>

On 22 March 2024, Rogers made his debut for the [[England national under-21 football team|England U21s]] during a 5–1 victory over [[Azerbaijan national under-21 football team|Azerbaijan]] in [[Baku]] during [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Report: Azerbaijan 1–5 England MU21s|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2024/Mar/22/england-mens-under-21s-azerbaijan-baku-match-report-20242203|access-date=25 March 2024|website=EnglandFootball.com}}</ref>

On 11 November 2024, Rogers was called up to the [[England national football team|England senior team]] for the first time for upcoming [[UEFA Nations League]] fixtures against [[Greece national football team|Greece]] and the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c39nr2x8324o |title=Rogers called into England squad as eight pull out |website=BBC Sport |date=11 November 2024 |access-date=13 November 2024}}</ref> The 22-year-old made his senior debut on 14 November as a second-half substitute in a 3–0 away victory against Greece.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 November 2024 |title=Greece vs. England – 14 November 2024 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2024/11/14/europe/uefa-nations-league/greece/england/4319434/ |access-date=14 November 2024 |website=Soccerway}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=England move top of Nations League group with dominant win in Greece |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cy4npdnyddzt |website=BBC Sport |access-date=15 November 2024 |date=14 November 2024}}</ref>

Rogers scored his first England goal in a 3–0 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] win over [[Wales national football team|Wales]] at [[Wembley Stadium|Wembley]] on 9 October 2025.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[BBC Sport]]|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cvg9j7lqvqvt|title=England 3–0 Wales|date=9 October 2025|access-date=10 October 2025|last1=McNulty|first1=Phil}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Rogers is a versatile player who has primarily operated as a [[Playmaker#Advanced playmakers|number 10]] at Aston Villa<ref>{{Cite web |title=How Rogers' direct style is driving Aston Villa forward |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4139797 |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=www.premierleague.com |date=5 October 2024 |language=en}}</ref> but can also play as a winger, striker or attacking midfielder.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last1=Tanswell |first1=Jacob |last2=Carey |first2=Mark |title=How Morgan Rogers has hit the ground running at Aston Villa |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5393630/2024/04/10/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-emery/ |access-date=2024-12-26 |work=The New York Times |date=10 April 2024 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Tactically, he is known to take long distance shots<ref name=":8" /> and engage in an aggressive style of attacking play, driving at opponents and breaking defensive lines.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clarke |first=Adrian |date=6 October 2024 |title=How Rogers' direct style is driving Aston Villa forward |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4139797 |access-date=8 August 2025 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Ben |date=30 August 2024 |title=Morgan Rogers: 'It is mad to know where I've got to in a short space of time' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/aug/30/morgan-rogers-the-training-was-a-shock-to-me-the-games-were-a-shock |access-date=8 August 2025 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref name=":10">{{Cite web |date=12 December 2025 |title=Ranked! The 20 best attacking midfielders in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/person/player/best-attacking-midfielders-in-the-world |access-date=16 December 2025 |website=FourFourTwo |language=en}}</ref> He has received praise for his physical strength,<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Benson |first=Ryan |date=2024-10-06 |title=Morgan Rogers: Robust Yet Graceful, Like a Raging Bull on Ice Skates |url=https://theanalyst.com/2024/10/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-rising-star |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=Opta Analyst |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news |title=Morgan Rogers: Aston Villa forward in the form of his life and impressing in Unai Emery's squad |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13227136/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-forward-in-the-form-of-his-life-and-impressing-in-unai-emerys-squad |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241206113829/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13227136/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-forward-in-the-form-of-his-life-and-impressing-in-unai-emerys-squad |archive-date=6 December 2024 |access-date=2024-12-26 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite news |title=Morgan Rogers' impact at Aston Villa: Strength, skill and the ideal fit for Unai Emery since signing in January |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11677/13122814/morgan-rogers-impact-at-aston-villa-strength-skill-and-the-ideal-fit-for-unai-emery-since-signing-in-january |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241202081833/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11677/13122814/morgan-rogers-impact-at-aston-villa-strength-skill-and-the-ideal-fit-for-unai-emery-since-signing-in-january |archive-date=2 December 2024 |access-date=2024-12-26 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref> powerful runs,<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":0" /> tactical intelligence,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-21 |title=Morgan Rogers: From Manchester City prospect to Pep Guardiola's tormentor |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cvgnvz78136o |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-26 |title=Report: Aston Villa's Rising Star Nears New Long-Term Contract Extension |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/report-aston-villas-rising-star-nears-new-long-term-contract-extension-40255601 |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> ability to score from a distance,<ref name=":13">{{Cite news |last=Wigmore |first=Tim |date=14 December 2025 |title=Morgan Rogers is winning his World Cup battle against Jude Bellingham |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2025/12/14/west-ham-vs-aston-villa-live-score-latest-premier-league/ |access-date=7 January 2026 |work=The Telegraph |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref><ref name=":12">{{Cite news |last=Tanswell |first=Jacob |date=7 January 2026 |title=The rise of Morgan Rogers: From Championship loans to one of Europe's best No 10s |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6921814/2026/01/07/morgan-rogers-aston-villa-spectacular-rise/ |access-date=7 January 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> dribbling<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":0" /> and work ethic.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |last=Churchill |first=Max |date=2025-03-01 |title=The 10 hardest-working players in the Premier League right now have been ranked – in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/hardest-working-players-premier-league-right-now/ |access-date=2025-03-25 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> His strength on the ball and dangerous runs have drawn media comparisons to [[Jamal Musiala]], [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]] and [[Wayne Rooney]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2024-09-14 |title=Aston Villa star given huge praise with comparison Bayern Munich hero |url=https://talksport.com/football/2053747/aston-villa-morgan-rogers-comparison-bayern-munich-jamal-musiala/ |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=talkSPORT |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref name=":8">{{Cite web |title=Morgan Rogers: The England attacker whose carrying skills are drawing comparisons to 'the real Ronaldo' |url=https://www.sportinglife.com/football/news/morgan-rogers-the-england-attacker-whose-carrying-skills-are-drawing-comparisons-to-the-real-ronaldo/221781 |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=www.sportinglife.com |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Wiseman |first=Ciaran |date=25 March 2025 |title=Hoddle compares Three Lions star to England hero after he did icon's skill move |url=https://talksport.com/football/3050767/glenn-hoddle-morgan-rogers-england/ |access-date=25 March 2025 |website=talkSPORT |language=en-gb}}</ref> Rogers himself has expressed admiration for Musiala, as well as [[Florian Wirtz]] and Villa teammate [[Jadon Sancho]].<ref name=":12" />

Described throughout 2025 as one of the best young players in the Premier League,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Stevenson |first=William |date=2025-01-21 |title=The 10 most exciting players in the Premier League have been named & ranked – in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/most-exciting-players-premier-league-right-now-ranked/ |access-date=2025-01-30 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Aston Villa set to hand new deals to Morgan Rogers, Jacob Ramsey |url=https://thehardtackle.com/transfer-news/2024/11/02/aston-villa-set-to-hand-new-deals-to-morgan-rogers-jacob-ramsey/ |access-date=2025-01-30 |website=TheHardTackle.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Diamond |first=Harry |date=2024-11-21 |title=Premier League Awards – The 2024/25 season so far! |url=https://thefootballfaithful.com/premier-league-awards-the-2024-25-season-so-far/ |access-date=2025-01-30 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-29 |title=Chris Sutton says Aston Villa star Morgan Rogers was 'unplayable' vs Celtic |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/chris-sutton-says-aston-villa-star-morgan-rogers-was-unplayable-vs-celtic-40634288 |access-date=2025-01-30 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-25 |title=Pourquoi le PSG doit se méfier de Morgan Rogers |url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/pourquoi-le-psg-doit-se-mefier-de-morgan-rogers-40977453 |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=OneFootball |language=fr}}</ref> media outlets began describing Rogers as one of the best attacking midfielders in the world during the [[2025–26 Aston Villa F.C. season|2025–26 season]], with both ''[[FourFourTwo]] and [[Sports Illustrated]]'' ranking him eighth in his position.<ref name=":10" /><ref name=":14">{{Cite web |date=22 July 2025 |title=The 25 Best Attacking Midfielders in World Soccer: Ranked |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-attacking-midfielders-in-world-soccer-ranked |access-date=4 August 2025 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref> ''Sports Illustrated'' described Rogers as an "anomaly" among attacking midfielders due to his physical strength,<ref name=":14" /> while ''[[ESPN]]'' included Rogers in twelfth on their 2025 ''FC 100'' list of the best attacking midfielders in the world, writing that Rogers "has it all – youth, power, intensity, skills, hunger, energy, confidence".<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 June 2025 |title=2025 FC 100: Bellingham among best attacking midfielders in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45178766/2025-fc-100-bellingham-best-attacking-midfielders-mens-soccer |access-date=8 August 2025 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> In the same year ''GiveMeSport'' wrote that his ball control was "one of, if not the best in the league".<ref name=":4" /> Owing to Rogers' performances, some media sources opined that Rogers could start for England at the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]] in the number 10 role, potentially keeping Jude Bellingham and [[Cole Palmer]] out of the starting eleven.<ref>{{Cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=12 November 2025 |title=Jude Bellingham and Morgan Rogers have 'friendly' England rivalry - but who will come out on top? |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c30vy02v7d8o |access-date=7 January 2026 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 December 2025 |title=Morgan Rogers responds to Jude Bellingham & Cole Palmer competition for England after Aston Villa ace continues hot streak with Man Utd double |url=https://www.foxsports.com/articles/soccer/morgan-rogers-responds-to-jude-bellingham-cole-palmer-competition-for-england-after-aston-villa-ace-continues-hot-streak-with-man-utd-double |access-date=7 January 2026 |website=www.foxsports.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ross-Murray |first=Ewan |date=22 December 2025 |title='Focused' England Star Breaks Silence on Jude Bellingham, World Cup No. 10 Debate |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/england-star-breaks-silence-jude-bellingham-world-cup-no10-debate |access-date=7 January 2026 |website=Sports Illustrated |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":11" /><ref name=":12" /><ref name=":13" />

After scoring, Rogers will often celebrate with an "ice cold" celebration<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Hepburn |first1=Daniel |last2=Ritchie |first2=Calum |last3=Jeevathayalan |first3=Vijievan |date=18 February 2023 |title=The 15 best midfielders in the Premier League right now have been ranked – in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/midfielders-premier-league-ranked/ |access-date=8 August 2025 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> where he crosses his arms and rubs his shoulders, a move later popularized by Rogers' former Manchester City teammate Cole Palmer; Palmer has attributed this move to Rogers, saying "My boy Morgz did one for Middlesbrough, so I told him I'd do it too if I scored."<ref>{{Cite web |title=The origins of Cole Palmer's 'cold' celebration |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4147118 |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=www.premierleague.com |date=20 October 2024 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-29 |title=The real reason why Morgan Rogers copies Cole Palmer's celebration has been revealed |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/football-news/aston-villa/morgan-rogers-celebration-chelsea-cole-palmer-021120-20240929 |access-date=2024-12-26 |website=SPORTbible |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Anyanwu |first=Finnian |date=20 October 2024 |title=The origins of Cole Palmer's 'cold' celebration |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4147118 |access-date=7 January 2026 |website=Premier League |language=en}}</ref>

